propBoundaryCount: Number of always visible pages at the beginning and end.
propClasses: Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
propDefaultPage: The page selected by default when the component is uncontrolled.
propGetItemAriaLabel:
Accepts a function which returns a string value that provides a user-friendly name for the current page.

For localization purposes, you can use the provided [translations](/guides/localization/).
propOnChange: Callback fired when the page is changed.
propShape: The shape of the pagination items.
propSiblingCount: Number of always visible pages before and after the current page.
propSize: The size of the pagination component.
stylesRoot: Styles applied to the root element.
stylesUl: Styles applied to the ul element.
stylesOutlined: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="outlined"`.
stylesText: Styles applied to the root element if `variant="text"`.
